President Obama has declared an emergency in the District of Columbia due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Sandy. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be provided with 75 percent federal funding. Steven S. Ward has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.